description:
Background:
Approved idea #5 and GitHub issue #14: delivery bead closure should line up with verified commits so agents cannot close work as done while code changes float uncommitted. The plan must avoid attestation drift: the final Burpvalve check has to run against the exact staged payload that will be committed, including .beads/issues.jsonl when a delivery bead is closed.

Goal:
Tie implementation/content/config/test bead delivery to Burpvalve verification and commit evidence, while keeping issue-only/admin work possible without fake commits.

Scope:
- Add guidance to README, AGENTS template, and Beads integration docs explaining delivery bead vs admin bead policy.
- Add commit metadata support such as burpvalve commit --bead <id> and repeated --bead flags, recording bead IDs in the attestation/report in a stable queryable JSON field.
- Add a non-mutating helper such as burpvalve beads plan-close <id> or burpvalve beads preflight <id> that prints the ordered sequence for delivery work:
  1. inspect/stage the intended implementation/docs/config/test payload;
  2. inspect required Burpvalve cells and gather verifier evidence for that work;
  3. close the delivery bead only after the work is ready;
  4. run br sync --flush-only;
  5. stage the implementation payload plus .beads/issues.jsonl and any intentional bead metadata files;
  6. run the final Burpvalve commit gate with --bead metadata against that exact staged payload;
  7. if Burpvalve generates an attestation before commit, stage it and rerun the final gate if needed so the attested payload and committed payload match.
- The helper must explicitly warn that any staged payload change after attestation generation requires rerunning Burpvalve.
- The helper must default to guidance/dry-run; it must not close beads, stage files, commit files, or mutate .beads.
- Support coupled delivery by allowing multiple bead IDs in feature metadata when the staged payload intentionally combines them, with an explicit rationale so unrelated work is not normalized.
- Support issue-only/admin work through explicit classification or flags; do not guess admin-only status from title text alone.
- Use the attestation query API to prove bead IDs are queryable rather than adding a parallel parser.
